{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "c3f1a2b4-d5e6-7f89-a0bc-de1234567890",
    "name": "Accenture Backend Challenge API",
    "description": "## Overview\nComplete API collection for the Accenture Backend Challenge — a reactive REST service built with Spring WebFlux and R2DBC PostgreSQL.\n\nThe API manages a two-level domain hierarchy:\n- **Franchise** — a top-level brand (e.g. a restaurant chain).\n- **Branch** — a physical location that belongs to exactly one franchise.\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start\n1. Start the application (`./gradlew bootRun`) and PostgreSQL (`docker compose up -d`).\n2. Verify the service is healthy using **03 - Health → 01 - Health Check**.\n3. Run **01 - Franchises → 01 - Create Franchise** — the returned `id` is automatically saved to the `{{franchiseId}}` collection variable.\n4. Run **02 - Branches → 01 - Create Branch** — the returned `id` is automatically saved to the `{{branchId}}` collection variable.\n5. All subsequent requests resolve `{{franchiseId}}` and `{{branchId}}` from those variables.\n\n---\n\n## Collection Variables\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `baseUrl` | `http://localhost:8080` | Base URL of the running server |\n| `franchiseId` | _(auto-set)_ | ID populated after Create Franchise |\n| `branchId` | _(auto-set)_ | ID populated after Create Branch |\n\n---\n\n## Common Response Codes\n| Code | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `200 OK` | Successful GET or PATCH |\n| `201 Created` | Successful POST (resource created) |\n| `404 Not Found` | Resource with the given ID does not exist |\n| `500 Internal Server Error` | Validation failure or unexpected error |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Base URL of the running API server. Change this to point at a different environment (e.g. staging)."
    },
    {
      "key": "franchiseId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "ID of the franchise currently under test. Automatically populated by the 'Create Franchise' request test script."
    },
    {
      "key": "branchId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "ID of the branch currently under test. Automatically populated by the 'Create Branch' request test script."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 - Franchises",
      "description": "Endpoints for managing franchises.\n\nA **franchise** is the top-level entity. Each franchise has a unique UUID (v7) generated server-side on creation and can hold zero or more branches.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "01 - Create Franchise",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "description": "Request body must be JSON"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Burger Palace\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/franchises",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "franchises"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a new franchise with the given name.\n\nThe server generates a UUID v7 as the franchise `id`. The `id` is captured automatically by the test script and stored in the `{{franchiseId}}` collection variable.\n\n**Validation rules:**\n- `name` must be present and non-blank; otherwise the server returns `500`.\n\n**Example request body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"Burger Palace\"\n}\n```\n\n**Example response (201):**\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"018f1a2b-3c4d-7e5f-a6b7-c8d9e0f1a2b3\",\n  \"name\": \"Burger Palace\",\n  \"branches\": null\n}\n```"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 201 Created', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains an id', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.id).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response name matches the request', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.name).to.eql('Burger Palace');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Auto-save the franchise id for subsequent requests",
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json && json.id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('franchiseId', json.id);",
                  "    console.log('franchiseId set to: ' + json.id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 - Franchise Created",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
